commentTextItems.html: a full toss driven past the bowler for two runs

commentPostTextItems.html: It's official.. the game has been abandoned.

commentTextItems.html: guided up to mid-on as Rahmat Shah brings up his maiden ODI 100. A superb knock that has been vital for Afghanistan's innings.
a short ball, pulled for six as they bring up their 150 partnership for the 5th wicket.

headshotImage.caption: Rahmat Shah player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rahmat Shah player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: a slower ball that goes down the leg side
another bouncer. This one is legitimate and his second for the over
bouncer goes over the wicket keeper
full toss, flicked into the leg side
Zadran smashes the free hit for six. Relatively quiet over since the rain break, only 10 off that one

commentTextItems.html: the ball slips out of Sharif's hand as the ball flies high above the batter. No ball and free hit coming up
glanced off the legs for a single. A good over for Scotland so far
a horrible overpitched delivery pulled for just a single.
driven to cover for a single
Zadrad should be out. He edges the ball in the air to the third man where Wallace seems to dive over the ball.

milestones.description: Zadran and Rahmat Shah's 157-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 125 between Mohammad Nabi and Samiullah Shinwari
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (4) in ODIs for AFG, going past Nawroz Mangal's 4

stories.title: Rain spoils Rahmat's ton, Najib's blitz
stories.subTitle: Scotland v Afghanistan, 1st ODI, Edinburgh
stories.seoTitle: Scotland v Afghanistan report - Rain spoils Rahmat Shah ton, Najibullah Zadran blitz
stories.summary: Scotland's first ODI at home in more than two years ended in frustrating fashion, with the first ODI of the two-match series against Afghanistan finishing with a no result
stories.byline: The Report by Peter Della Penna in Edinburgh
